 1390                                                       ;If the line in the LINE INPUT BUFFER has a line num-
 1391                                                       ;ber then the line is to be placed in the USER PRO-
 1392                                                       ;GRAM BUFFER. It is now necessary to determine
 1393                                                       ;where the new line is to be placed in the USER PRO-
 1394                                                       ;GRAM BUFFER. This is dictated by the value of the
 1395                                                       ;new line number in relation to the line numbers cur-
 1396                                                       ;rently in the program buffer. The next portion of the
 1397                                                       ;program goes through the contents of the USER PRO-
 1398                                                       ;GRAM BUFFER comparing the values of the line num-
 1399                                                       ;bers already stored against the value of the line number
 1400                                                       ;currently being held in the LINE INPUT BUFFER.
 1401                                                       ;Appropriate action is then taken to Insert or Append,
 1402                                                       ;Change, or Delete a line in the program buffer.
